  "correctAnswer": "Write a product description for a smartwatch that is targeted specifically at fitness enthusiasts. The description should be approximately 150 words — not significantly shorter or longer. Highlight the features that matter most to someone who is serious about fitness, such as heart rate monitoring, GPS tracking, workout modes, sleep tracking, and battery life. Use energetic, motivating, and confident language that speaks directly to someone who is passionate about their health and performance. Avoid generic tech language — focus on how each feature helps the user train harder, recover better, and reach their fitness goals faster. The description should make a fitness enthusiast feel like this smartwatch was made specifically for them and that they cannot perform at their best without it.",
  "explanation": "A product description prompt needs three things to work well — a word limit, a target audience, and a focus on benefits rather than just features. The word limit of 150 words keeps the description tight and suitable for a product page — too short and it feels incomplete, too long and customers stop reading. Specifying 'fitness enthusiasts' as the audience tells the AI to focus on features that this specific group cares about, like GPS and heart rate monitoring, rather than generic smartwatch features. The most important instruction here is to focus on how the features help the user — not just what the features are. Customers do not buy features, they buy results. This prompt pushes the AI to write copy that connects emotionally with the reader and makes them feel the product was built for their exact lifestyle."
