  "type": "prompt-writing",
  "text": "Design a prompt that creates a blog introduction with a hook and a question to engage readers.",
  "options": [],
  "correctIndex": -1,
  "keywords": "blog introduction, hook, question",
  "correctAnswer": "Write a blog introduction that starts with a strong hook — one bold, surprising, or thought-provoking sentence that immediately grabs the reader's attention and makes them curious to read more. After the hook, write 2 to 3 sentences that briefly set up the topic and give the reader a reason to keep reading. End the introduction with a compelling question that speaks directly to the reader's experience or curiosity — a question they genuinely want to know the answer to. The entire introduction should feel conversational and engaging, not stiff or formal. Keep it under 100 words so it is short enough to pull the reader in without giving too much away.",
  "explanation": "A blog introduction has one job — to stop the reader from clicking away. This is why the structure of the introduction matters so much. Starting with a hook grabs attention in the first second, the middle sentences build enough context to make the topic feel relevant, and ending with a question creates curiosity that pulls the reader into the rest of the article. Without telling the AI all three of these structural elements, it might write a perfectly fine introduction that still fails to engage the reader because it starts too slowly or ends too flatly. The 100-word limit is also an important instruction — blog introductions that are too long lose the reader before the actual content even begins. Every part of this prompt has a purpose, and together they give the AI a clear blueprint for writing an introduction that actually works."
