  "correctAnswer": "Generate 3 variations of an email subject line and preview text pair for a product discount campaign. Each variation should have a different approach — one should lead with the discount amount to immediately grab attention with a clear offer, one should create urgency by focusing on a deadline or limited availability, and one should spark curiosity by hinting at the deal without giving everything away so the reader is compelled to open the email. For each variation, the subject line should be under 50 characters so it displays fully on all devices including mobile phones, and the preview text should be under 90 characters and add new information that supports the subject line rather than just repeating it. The tone across all 3 variations should feel exciting and personal — like a message from a brand that genuinely wants the reader to benefit from this deal.",
  "explanation": "The subject line and preview text are the two most important elements of any marketing email because they are the only things the reader sees before deciding whether to open the email or delete it. Most people check their emails on their phones, which means a subject line that is too long gets cut off and loses its impact — this is why the 50-character limit is not just a suggestion but a real technical constraint. The preview text is often wasted by brands who simply repeat the subject line — but a smart preview text adds a second reason to open the email, which significantly increases open rates. Asking for 3 variations with different approaches — discount-led, urgency-led, and curiosity-led — gives you real options to test against each other, which is exactly how professional email marketers work. Testing different subject line styles is one of the fastest ways to learn what your specific audience responds to."
