  "correctAnswer": "Write a product description that is fully optimized for SEO. Before writing the description, identify 3 to 5 relevant SEO keywords that a potential customer would realistically type into Google when searching for this type of product. Then write a description of 150 to 200 words that naturally includes these keywords in a way that feels smooth and readable — do not stuff the keywords in awkwardly or repeat them too many times, as this hurts SEO rather than helping it. The description should lead with the most important benefit of the product in the first sentence, since search engines give more weight to content that appears early in the text. Use simple, clear language that both search engines and real customers can understand easily. End the description with a subtle call-to-action that encourages the reader to take the next step without sounding too pushy.",
  "explanation": "Writing a product description for SEO is very different from writing one just for customers — you have to satisfy two audiences at the same time. The search engine needs to find relevant keywords in the right places to rank the page higher in search results, and the human reader needs to feel like the description was written naturally and helpfully for them. This is why keyword stuffing — forcing too many keywords into a description — is one of the most common and damaging mistakes beginners make. It makes the writing feel unnatural to readers and actually gets penalized by Google. Asking the AI to identify keywords first and then write around them naturally is the correct SEO approach. The instruction to lead with the most important benefit in the first sentence is also a real SEO technique — search engines scan the beginning of content more heavily, so putting your strongest keyword and message first gives the page a better chance of ranking higher in search results."
