  "correctAnswer": "Write a detailed SEO-optimized product description for a women's wide-leg linen trouser listed on an independent online fashion store targeting style-conscious shoppers aged 25 to 45 who search for specific garment attributes rather than brand names, meaning the primary search intent the description must capture includes queries like 'wide leg linen trousers women,' 'high waist linen pants summer,' and 'breathable trousers for hot weather' — with a secondary intent around the garment's versatility for queries like 'linen trousers office to evening' and 'smart casual linen pants women.' The description must be 220 to 260 words, structured into three unlabeled paragraphs, and written in a warm but direct editorial voice that treats the reader as someone who knows what she wants and needs the description to confirm the garment will deliver it rather than persuade her from scratch. The first paragraph must open with the primary keyword phrase 'wide-leg linen trousers' within the first eight words, describe the garment's most commercially relevant physical attributes — a high elasticated waistband, a 32-inch inseam, belt loops, two side pockets and one rear pocket, and a fabric composition of 100 percent stonewashed European linen — and use at least two of the target keyword phrases naturally within the copy without forcing them into positions where they interrupt the reading experience. The second paragraph must address fit, feel, and wearability in sensory and practical terms — how the linen drapes and moves, how the stonewashing affects the hand and the break-in period, and the specific body types and heights the cut flatters — including the long-tail keyword phrase 'breathable trousers for hot weather' once and 'linen pants summer' once. The third paragraph must handle styling and versatility, describing two specific outfit contexts — one casual and one smart — that support the secondary keyword intent around office-to-evening wear, and close with a single sentence that introduces the available colorways: chalk white, warm sand, and faded sage. Follow the description with a separate SEO metadata block containing a page title of no more than 60 characters that leads with the primary keyword, a meta description of no more than 155 characters that includes the primary keyword and a benefit-driven hook, and five additional long-tail keyword phrases the product page should target in its image alt text and structured data.",

  "explanation": "A vague prompt like 'write a detailed product description optimized for SEO keywords for an online fashion store' produces a generic garment description that either stuffs keyword phrases so aggressively that the copy reads as machine-generated and drives customers away, or writes fluent marketing prose that buries the keywords in positions where search engines weight them minimally, failing at both the commercial and the SEO objective simultaneously. Naming the specific garment as a wide-leg linen trouser and identifying the exact search queries the description must capture — 'wide leg linen trousers women,' 'high waist linen pants summer,' 'breathable trousers for hot weather' — is the most important instruction because SEO copywriting without defined target keywords is not SEO copywriting at all, it is marketing writing that happens to contain some relevant words, and the difference between those two things is the difference between a product page that ranks on page one and one that ranks on page four. The instruction to place the primary keyword within the first eight words of the description is a technical SEO instruction that reflects how search engine crawlers weight keyword position — early placement in the body copy signals topical relevance more strongly than mid-paragraph placement, and a product description that opens with 'Effortlessly chic and perfect for warm days' before mentioning what the product actually is wastes the highest-value real estate in the copy. Requiring the description to be structured into three paragraphs with specific jobs — physical attributes in paragraph one, fit and feel in paragraph two, styling and versatility in paragraph three — is a content architecture instruction that serves both SEO and conversion simultaneously, because search engines reward topically organized content and customers make purchase decisions in exactly that sequence, first confirming the product is what they searched for, then evaluating whether it will fit and feel right, then imagining themselves wearing it. The instruction to include a separate metadata block with a page title under 60 characters and a meta description under 155 characters treats SEO as a complete technical discipline rather than a copywriting style, because a product description that is beautifully optimized in the body copy but has a page title that exceeds the search engine display limit will be truncated in search results in a way that cuts off the keyword and defeats the entire optimization effort."
