  "correctAnswer": "Please write a data-backed case study about a mid-sized e-commerce business that improved its ROI after switching to automated email marketing. Structure the case study in five sections: start with a client background of two to three sentences that describes the business, its size, and the specific problem it was facing before the solution was introduced. Then write a challenges section that names exactly what was going wrong — use specific numbers wherever possible such as cart abandonment rate, cost per acquisition, or monthly revenue loss — and do not use vague statements like 'the company was struggling' without backing them with a figure. Next write a solution section that explains what was implemented, how long it took, and what the setup involved. Then write a results section that leads with the most impressive ROI figure and supports it with at least three additional metrics such as percentage increase in repeat purchases, reduction in cost per email, or growth in monthly revenue — present every number as a specific figure and not a range. End with a one paragraph takeaway that explains why this result happened and what other businesses in a similar situation can learn from it. Do not invent statistics — if you do not have real data, clearly label the numbers as illustrative examples so the reader is never misled.",

