  "text": "Design a prompt that generates a full seasonal fashion campaign including theme narrative, color palette, mood board inspiration, and brand message.",
  "options": [],
  "correctIndex": -1,
  "keywords": "seasonal fashion campaign, theme narrative, color palette, mood board, brand message",
  "correctAnswer": "Generate a complete seasonal fashion campaign for a contemporary clothing brand. The campaign should cover the following sections in full detail. For the theme narrative, write a rich and evocative story of 3 to 4 sentences that captures the emotional world and visual universe of this season's collection — the narrative should make the reader feel the mood, the setting, and the kind of person who would wear this collection, not just describe what the clothes look like. For the color palette, identify 5 specific colors that define the season's look, give each color a creative and evocative name that fits the campaign theme rather than a generic color name, and explain in one sentence why each color was chosen and what feeling or image it evokes. For the mood board inspiration, describe 6 to 8 specific visual references that a creative director would use to inspire the campaign — these could include a type of landscape, a film, an art movement, a texture, a time of day, or a cultural moment — and for each reference explain in one sentence how it connects to the campaign's overall feeling. For the brand message, write one powerful campaign tagline of under 10 words that captures the entire season's spirit, followed by 2 to 3 sentences of supporting brand copy that expands on the tagline and speaks directly to the target customer's identity and aspirations. The entire campaign should feel cohesive — every section should feel like it belongs to the same creative world.",
  "explanation": "A seasonal fashion campaign is one of the most creatively complex briefs a brand can produce because it needs to work on multiple levels simultaneously — it must tell a story, evoke a feeling, define a visual language, and communicate a brand identity all at the same time, and every element must feel like it belongs to the same creative universe. Without specifying exactly what each section should contain and how detailed it should be, the AI will produce a surface-level campaign that lists a few colors and a generic tagline but fails to create the kind of immersive creative direction that a real fashion brand needs to brief its photographers, stylists, designers, and copywriters. The instruction to give each color an evocative name rather than a generic one — for example 'Dusk Terracotta' instead of just 'orange' — is a small but critical detail that separates a professional fashion campaign from an amateur one, because color naming in fashion is a creative act that sets the emotional tone of the entire collection. The mood board section is especially important because it gives the creative team a shared visual language to work from — without specific references, every person on the team will imagine the campaign differently and the final output will feel inconsistent. The cohesion instruction at the end is the most important overarching requirement because a fashion campaign where the color palette feels disconnected from the narrative, or the tagline feels unrelated to the mood board, will fail to create the unified brand impression that turns a seasonal collection into a cultural moment."
