  "type": "prompt-writing",
  "text": "Write a prompt that generates a data-driven e-commerce fashion strategy including SEO, conversion optimization, and product storytelling.",
  "options": [],
  "correctIndex": -1,
  "keywords": "e-commerce fashion strategy, SEO, conversion optimization, product storytelling",
  "correctAnswer": "Generate a comprehensive data-driven e-commerce fashion strategy that covers three interconnected areas — SEO, conversion optimization, and product storytelling. For the SEO section, identify the types of keywords a fashion e-commerce brand should target at three different levels — broad discovery keywords that attract new shoppers who are just browsing, category-specific keywords that attract shoppers who know what type of product they want, and long-tail keywords that attract high-intent shoppers who are ready to buy. Explain how each type of keyword should be used differently across product pages, category pages, and blog content to build a complete SEO architecture that drives organic traffic at every stage of the customer journey. For the conversion optimization section, identify the 5 most common reasons fashion shoppers abandon a product page without buying — such as uncertainty about sizing, lack of styling inspiration, insufficient product images, unclear return policy, or slow page load times — and for each reason provide a specific and practical fix the brand can implement to reduce abandonment and increase the percentage of visitors who complete a purchase. For the product storytelling section, explain how to write product descriptions that go beyond listing fabric and dimensions — each description should tell a mini story about who the garment was designed for, what occasion it is perfect for, and how it will make the wearer feel, so the customer can picture themselves in the product before they buy. End the strategy with a priority action plan that lists the top 5 things the brand should implement first to get the fastest and most measurable improvement in online sales.",
  "explanation": "E-commerce fashion strategy is uniquely challenging because fashion purchasing is an almost entirely emotional decision that happens in a digital environment built on data and logic — and a successful strategy has to bridge both worlds simultaneously. Most fashion brands either focus heavily on aesthetics and storytelling while ignoring SEO and conversion data, or they optimize obsessively for search rankings while producing product pages that feel cold and uninspiring. Neither approach works on its own. The three-level keyword structure in the SEO section is important because most brands only target one type of keyword and miss the customers who are at different stages of their buying journey — a shopper browsing for 'summer outfits' needs to find the brand at the discovery stage, while a shopper searching for 'linen wide-leg trousers under 80 pounds' is ready to buy immediately and needs to land directly on the right product page. The conversion optimization section addresses the specific friction points that are unique to fashion e-commerce — unlike buying a book or a software subscription, buying clothes online involves a high level of uncertainty about fit, appearance, and feel that no amount of good photography can completely eliminate, which is why addressing each source of uncertainty directly on the product page is so critical to reducing abandonment. The product storytelling section is what ties the data-driven elements together with the emotional reality of fashion — a customer who can picture themselves wearing a garment in a specific moment of their life is far more likely to add it to their cart than one who is simply reading a list of fabric specifications and measurements."
